   author = "J. B. Boyce and J. C. Mikkelsen and B. A. Huberman",
   abstract = "We have examined both the ionic conductivity and the NMR line narrowing in two channel-structured superionic conductors in the light of Richards' one-dimensional theory. For Li2Ti3O7 the ionic conductivity is not sufficiently anisotropic to explain the observed small NMR prefactor in terms of i-D effects. For β-LiAlSiO4 the NMR line narrowing in the crossover region does not yield the predicted large change in the activation energy given by the 1-D theory."
